reviews.text:
We ordered here once for a work lunch and loved it so much that it‚Äôs now part of our regular rotation. I placed a late order for 15 people, and they still accommodated us without issue. The staff was friendly, the location was clean, and I really appreciated that each meal was boxed individually.

Their team is extremely courteous, and the entire experience was seamless. The food was hot, fresh, and prepared right on time, not too early or too late, so we were able to enjoy it while it was still perfectly hot back at the office.

As for the food itself, 10/10. The spice levels range from no spice to hot, so everyone had options, and the fries were delicious. Their lemonades were also a big hit. Overall, amazing service, great food, and a perfect spot for both individual meals and work events. Highly recommend!

The good was good but not great. Some of the chicken nuggets were tiny and dry pieces. Tje fries were really crispy and yummy. The sauces are 1.00 each. Love that they were open late (12 am) so we could sit down and eat.

I got the medium spice, and it was spicy enough that I don't see how anyone would enjoy anything spicier.  It was hot, fresh, and delicious.  I really appreciated how it was a dry rub versus a sauce that it was drenched in.  My only complaint is the price, once you add in a drink (not included for some reason) it's almost $20 for one person.  Plus they ask for a tip, which is crazy for a fast food place that's already pricey.

Houston Hot Chicken has to be one of my favorite places to eat!  The food is SO GOOD.

Ken is the manager of a few of the local locations and he is awesome.  Autumn at the Lehi main location has great customer service skills and deserves to be recognized!

We will be back!

Great new place to try. It seems to me that they are a restaurant with an emphasis on spicy chicken. We had a large order so we got a little bit of everything. Everybody loved their chicken. I personally felt my chicken was dry but the sausage and the pickle helped.

Some people had the loaded and fusion fries. Both said it was really good. But both said it could use more sauce! You can't go wrong with more sauce! Unless it gets soggy ü§™.

We also tried the "lift off" and it did have some kick to it. But I survivedüòÖ. So if you're looking for fun flavor and good food this is a stop you will want to make.

recentReviews.author: Casey Swain
recentReviews.text:
Great new place to try. It seems to me that they are a restaurant with an emphasis on spicy chicken. We had a large order so we got a little bit of everything. Everybody loved their chicken. I personally felt my chicken was dry but the sausage and the pickle helped.

Some people had the loaded and fusion fries. Both said it was really good. But both said it could use more sauce! You can't go wrong with more sauce! Unless it gets soggy ü§™.

We also tried the "lift off" and it did have some kick to it. But I survivedüòÖ. So if you're looking for fun flavor and good food this is a stop you will want to make.
